5|$|Prior to the {{dominance}} of the Gelug sect <b>of</b> <b>Buddhism</b> in Tawang, the Nyingmapa or the Black Hat sect <b>of</b> <b>Buddhism</b> was dominant and this resulted in their hegemony and even hostile approach towards the founder, Merek Lama. This problem was compounded by the Drukpas of Bhutan, who also belonged to the Nyingmapa sect, who even tried to invade and take control of Tawang. Hence, when the Tawang monastery was built like a fort structure, a strategic location was chosen from the defense point of view.|$|E
